article_title: Regulators Slam Investor Proposal to Pay for Teachers' Life Insurance
article_text:
Florida insurance regulators have expressed "significant doubts" about an unusual proposal from a consulting firm to provide life insurance to thousands of Florida teachers, paid for by investors.

The Pasco County School District had been considering the offer, with a decision hinging on the opinion of the state's Office of Insurance...

twitter.description: An investor plan to provide free life insurance for teachers appeared too good to be true after Florida regulators listed "significant doubts" about the program
